casebody.data:
The HYDRAULIC PRESS CORP. et al. v. Elek K. BENEDEK. No. 7493. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Feb. 11, 1937. Toulmin & Toulmin, of Dayton, Ohio, and Day, Young & Veach, of Qeveland, Ohio, for appellant. J. Harrow Leonard, of Cleveland, Ohio, J. D. Sears, of Bucyrus, Ohio, Walter Dressel, of Mt. Gilead, Ohio, and Albert R. Golrick, of Qeveland, Ohio, for appellees.

Before HICKS, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon application of appellant the appeal in the above-entitled case is dismissed, at appellant’s costs.
